          "stem": "按要求完成应用文写作。",
          "body": "Directions\nYou have just come back from the U.S. as a member of a Sino-American cultural exchange program. Write a letter to your American colleague to\nexpress your thanks for his/her warm reception;welcome him/her to visit China in due course.\nYou should write about 100 words on ANSWER SHEET 2.\nDo not sign your own name at the end of the letter. Use “Zhang Wei” instead.\nDo not write your address. (10 points)",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "解析一、要点归纳应用文类型：书信。需注意格式完整，包括称呼、正文、结尾敬语及署名。语言风格：收信人为美国同事，用语不必过于正式，保持礼貌、亲切即可。内容要点：表达对美国同事热情接待的感谢；为使感谢更自然，可适当回顾对方的款待细节，提及在对方帮助下的收获；最后诚挚邀请对方在合适的时候访问中国。二、范文参考Dear [Friend’s Name],Thank you very much for your warm reception during my visit to the U.S. as a delegate of the Sino-American cultural exchange program. Your thoughtful arrangements made me feel completely at home. With your detailed explanations of American customs, I was able to quickly overcome culture shock and gain a deeper understanding of your culture. I truly appreciate everything you did for me.I sincerely welcome you to visit China in due course. It would be my great pleasure to reciprocate your kindness and show you around. I am sure you will have a wonderful experience and gain rich insights into Chinese culture.Looking forward to your visit!Yours sincerely,Zhang Wei三、写作储备1. 传达谢意express gratitude 表达感恩Gratitude is the sign of noble souls. 感恩是高尚灵魂的象征。With sincere appreciation, I would like to thank you. 我要带着真诚的谢意感谢你。Life is so much easier with great friends like you. 有你这么好的朋友，生活变得更加轻松。Your support has made me a strong and driven individual, and I will forever be grateful to you. 你的支持让我成为一个坚强而奋发向上的人，我将永远对你心存感激。2. 感谢信常用表达开头语：I really appreciate your hospitality during my visit to…Thank you for all the help you have given me with my…I wish to express my heartfelt thanks to you for…I want you to know how much I appreciate your…发展部分：You helped me to…You taught me to…结束语：I truly appreciate your help.Thanks again for your hospitality.Thank you for your consideration.",
