          "body": "Directions\nWrite an essay based on the following table. In your writing, you should\ndescribe the table, andgive your comments.\nYou should write at least 150 words.\nWrite your essay on ANSWER SHEET 2. (15 points)\n（某公司员工工作满意度调查\n满意度\\年龄组满意 不清楚不满意≤40岁 16.7% 50.0% 33.3% 41-50岁 0.0% 36.0% 64.0% ＞50岁 40.0% 50.0% 10.0%",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "【现象解读】该表格反映了不同年龄段员工在工作满意度上的显著差异。这种现象与各年龄群体的职场处境及职业预期密切相关，需结合其各自特点进行分析。值得注意的是，即便在满意度最高的组别中，也仅有40%的员工表示满意，这表明有必要引导员工树立积极观念，以提升整体工作满意度。【范文参考】The table clearly illustrates the disparities in job satisfaction across different age groups. Employees over 50 years old reported the highest level of satisfaction, with 40% expressing contentment. In contrast, only 16.7% of those aged 40 or younger claimed to be satisfied, while 33.3% explicitly expressed dissatisfaction. The most pronounced dissatisfaction was observed among employees aged 41 to 50: none reported satisfaction, and an overwhelming 64% indicated they were dissatisfied.These variations can be attributed to distinct career stages and expectations. Employees in their 40s often face a career plateau—lacking the vigor of younger colleagues and the seniority of older professionals—which fosters a sense of stagnation and powerlessness, leading to high dissatisfaction. Younger employees, although sometimes uncertain about their career path, generally experience upward momentum, contributing to relatively higher morale. Meanwhile, older employees, having achieved career maturity and looking forward to retirement, tend to exhibit the greatest satisfaction.Overall, the data suggest that career challenges affect all age groups. Cultivating a positive attitude is essential for sustaining long-term job satisfaction.【写作储备】【话题表达补充】影响工作满意度的因素包括：Career advance opportunities（职业发展机会）Relationship with management（与领导层的关系）Relationship with co-workers（与同事的关系）Work environment（工作环境）Organization’s financial stability（组织的财务稳定性）Benefits（福利待遇）【写作素材积累】Organizations recognize that employee job satisfaction and engagement are crucial to sustainable business development.Employee satisfaction and engagement are influenced by a range of personal and professional factors, including life circumstances, career context, expectations, and values.Employees consistently seek competitive compensation, a supportive work atmosphere, and flexibility in the workplace.",
