          "stem": "按要求完成图表作文。",
          "body": "Directions\nWrite an essay based on the following chart. In your writing, you should\ninterpret the chart, andgive your comments.\nYou should write about 150 words on the ANSWER SHEET. (15 points)\n（图表标题为 “某高校学生兼职情况”，纵轴为 “人数百分比”，横轴为大学年级（大一、大二、大三、大四）。各年级学生兼职的人数百分比分别为：大一 67.77%、大二 71.13%、大三 71.93%、大四 88.24%。）",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "现象解读该图表直观展示了某高校学生兼职比例随年级变化的情况。数据显示，从大一到大四，学生兼职的比例持续上升，具体为：大一（67.77%）、大二（71.13%）、大三（71.93%）、大四（88.24%）。其中，大四阶段的兼职比例增幅最为显著。这一趋势主要源于高年级学生对于积累实践经验、为未来就业做准备的需求日益增强。此外，随着年级升高，学习与社会活动开支增加，经济因素也可能成为学生选择兼职的动机之一。然而，兼职现象的普遍化也潜藏着影响学业的隐患。在肯定兼职价值的同时，也需关注其可能造成的学习时间被挤压等问题。范文参考The bar chart illustrates the percentage of university students engaging in part-time jobs across different academic years. The figures show a consistent upward trend, starting at 67.77% among freshmen and rising to 88.24% among seniors. The most notable jump occurs in the final year.This increase can be largely attributed to students’ growing desire to gain practical experience in preparation for their future careers. Given the competitive job market, such preparation is both reasonable and prudent. Financial considerations also play a role, as higher academic years often entail greater expenses for study materials and social activities, motivating students to earn extra income.While part-time work can be beneficial, it is important to consider the potential risk of reduced study time. To maximize the benefits without compromising academic performance, students should strive to maintain a balance between work and studies.写作储备【话题表达补充】兼职目的：relieve the economic burden on their families, become financially capable of traveling and socializing, gain insight into real society, put knowledge into practice, enjoy a flexible schedule兼职可能遇到的问题：reduction in time available for studies, encountering scams or fraud, infringement of personal rights【写作素材积累】The number of students working in part-time jobs has grown significantly in sectors such as retail, hospitality, and other consumer service industries.The increasingly complex transition from education to employment has led more students to participate in the part-time labor market.Hiring student workers is often viewed by organizations as a flexible staffing solution.Industries such as restaurants, retail, and hospitality, as well as labor-intensive sectors, frequently rely on part-time employees to control payroll costs.",
