          "stem": "按要求完成图表作文。",
          "body": "Directions\nWrite an essay based on the following chart. In your writing, you should\ninterpret the chart, andgive your comments.\nYou should write about 150 words on the ANSWER SHEET. (15 points)\n（图表信息：标题为 “20 年间中国城镇人口与乡村人口变化图”；图例中，斜线柱代表城镇人口，空心柱代表乡村人口；数据（单位：百万）：1990 年：城镇人口 300，乡村人口 834；2000 年：城镇人口 458，乡村人口 807；2010 年：城镇人口 666，乡村人口 674。）",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "现象解读从1990年至2010年，中国总人口呈温和增长，但人口分布发生了显著变化。城镇人口从3亿大幅上升至6.7亿，而乡村人口则从8.2亿下降至6.8亿。在此期间，城乡人口差距明显缩小。范文参考Between 1990 and 2010, China experienced a moderate increase in total population, yet a dramatic shift occurred in population distribution. Urban population rose significantly from 300 million to 670 million, while rural population declined from 820 million to 680 million.This narrowing gap can be attributed to urbanization and unequal economic opportunities. Over these two decades, urban expansion led many rural residents to become city dwellers, either passively or by choice. At the same time, limited economic prospects in rural areas kept many peasants near the poverty line, motivating young and able-bodied individuals to migrate to cities for better livelihoods.The rise in urban population reflects economic progress, yet challenges remain. Many newcomers struggle to integrate due to limited education and urban habits, leaving them marginalized despite urban prosperity. Therefore, beyond celebrating these figures, efforts must focus on fostering inclusive development for all urban residents.写作储备【话题表达补充】城市化的表现：skyscraper（摩天大楼），meticulously planned city layouts（精细规划的城市布局），largest shopping mall（最大购物中心），“gigantic engine” for growth（增长的巨大引擎）城市化的问题：mobile urban residents（城市流动人口），rural migrants（农村移民），growing social tensions（日益加剧的社会矛盾），spread of slums（贫民窟蔓延）【写作素材积累】Thanks mainly to a tide of migration, China’s urban population had grown by more than 500 million since the reforms began—equivalent to the entire population of the United States plus three Britains.The harsh treatment of China’s internal migrants is creating huge social divisions that could erupt in serious unrest.As economic growth slows and the pool of surplus labor in the countryside shrinks, the pace of urbanization will diminish.",
