          "body": "Directions\nWrite an essay based on the following chart. In your writing, you should\ninterpret the chart, andgive your comments.\nYou should write about 150 words on the ANSWER SHEET. (15 points)\n（图表标题：我国某市居民春节假期花销比例\n饼图构成：新年礼物：40%,交通：20%,聚会吃饭：20%,其他：20%）",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "【现象解读】 聚会和送礼均属于人情交往的开销。交通费用除可能包含旅游开支外，更主要的是用于返乡团圆。整体来看，居民春节花销中绝大部分与人情往来相关，这与春节作为传统团圆节日的文化属性高度契合。【范文参考】The pie chart illustrates the distribution of residents’ spending during the Spring Festival in a city in China. Expenditure is divided into four categories: New Year gifts (40%), transportation (20%), gatherings and meals (20%), and other expenses (20%). Together, the first three categories account for 80% of the total spending.A significant portion of the expenses is related to social and familial interactions. This aligns with the nature of the Spring Festival as a time for family reunions and strengthening relationships. Investing in relationships is not only meaningful but also brings emotional satisfaction.However, it is important to avoid going to extremes. Some individuals may overspend in an attempt to display wealth or status, leading to unnecessary financial strain. Such behavior often results in waste and adds economic pressure. True value lies not in lavish spending, but in genuine connection and happiness. Therefore, rational and thoughtful consumption is encouraged during the festive season.【思路框架】第一段：描述图表基本信息，概括主要开支类别及比例。第二段：分析开支背后的文化与社会意义，强调人情往来与节日传统的关系。第三段：进行辩证评论，指出应避免盲目攀比，提倡理性消费，回归节日本质。【写作素材积累】The Spring Festival, similar to Christmas in the West, is the most significant occasion for family reunions in China. The travel rush around this period reflects the deep-rooted cultural emphasis on returning home.On Spring Festival Eve, families gather for a lavish dinner that includes symbolic dishes such as chicken, fish, and tofu, which represent good fortune, abundance, and prosperity.",
