          "body": "Directions\nWrite an essay based on the chart below. In your writing, you should\ninterpret the chart, andgive your comments.\nYou should write about 150 words on the ANSWER SHEET. (15 points)\n（该图表标题为“2013-2015年我国博物馆数量和参观人数”，展示了2013至2015年期间我国博物馆数量与参观人数的变化情况：\n博物馆数量（以菱形标记）：2013年约4000家，2014年略有增长，2015年保持在约4500家，整体呈小幅增长后趋于稳定的态势。\n参观人数（以方形标记，单位：十万人次）：2013年约6000，2014年增长至约7000，2015年进一步升至约8000，呈现持续上升的趋势。）",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "【现象解读】图表清晰展示了2013至2015年间我国博物馆数量与参观人次的变化趋势。两条折线均呈上升态势，反映出我国文化事业的蓬勃发展。具体而言：参观人数（方形标记） 持续快速增长，从2013年的约6亿人次增至2015年的约8亿人次，表明公众的文化需求日益旺盛。博物馆数量（菱形标记） 虽整体增长，但增速在后期放缓，从快速增长过渡到相对稳定。这一变化与参观人数的持续高增长形成对比，提示了潜在的挑战：若参观热度不减，现有的博物馆资源未来可能面临“供不应求”的压力。考生在论述时，可基于此数据变化阐发个人见解，或深入分析现象背后的成因。【参考范文】The given chart illustrates the consecutive growth in both the number of museums and museum visitors in China from 2013 to 2015. It is noteworthy that while the growth in museum numbers slowed down after 2014, the number of visitors maintained a strong upward trend.This phenomenon can be attributed to several factors. Firstly, national efforts in promoting cultural undertakings have led to the construction of numerous museums, many of which offer free admission to the public. Secondly, China’s rapid economic development has underpinned this cultural progress. As living standards improve, public demand for diverse spiritual enrichment grows, making museum visits an increasingly popular choice.However, this encouraging trend also presents challenges. The slowing growth in museum supply may struggle to meet the rapidly increasing and diversifying public demand for exhibitions. To address this, museums can enhance their efficiency and reach by embracing digital technologies, such as developing online “e-museums.” Through digital images and interactive videos, visitors can access countless exhibits globally and enjoy fresh experiences. It is believed that through such joint efforts, China’s museums will become a stronger driving force for cultural development and an important means of enhancing public well-being, thereby further boosting socio-economic progress.【写作储备】[话题表述补充]关于文化：civilization (n.) 文明bright / promising (a.) 光明的，有前途的cultural exchange / contact 文化交流community / grassroots culture 社区/草根文化cultural troupe 文化团体关于发展：scale (n.) 规模input (u./n.) 投入rejuvenation / renaissance (n.) 复兴reinforce / facilitate / empower (v.) 巩固，促进steadily step up 稳定增长scale up / down 大规模增加/减少yield good results 取得良好成效[写作素材积累]“The value of culture is its effect on character. It avails nothing unless it enables and strengthens that. Its aim is not beauty but goodness.” — Somerset Maugham （文化的价值在于它对人类品性的影响。除非文化能使品性更为高尚、有力，否则并无作用。它的目标不是美，而是善。 — 毛姆）Up to today, an integrated, open, competition-based and orderly cultural market system has been established in China. （时至今日，一个综合、开放、竞争有序的文化市场体系已在中国建立。）In line with the principle of “letting a hundred flowers blossom and a hundred schools of thoughts contend”, great efforts have been made to inherit and promote the fine traditional cultures of China and actively absorb the",
