          "body": "Directions\nSuppose you have to cancel your travel plan and will not be able to visit Professor Smith. Write him an email to\napologize and explain the situation, andsuggest a future meeting.\nYou should write about 100 words on the ANSWER SHEET.\nDo not use your own name. Use “Li Ming” instead.\nDo not write your address. (10 points)",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "【归纳要点】格式要求：书信（道歉信），需包含称呼、正文、结尾敬语及署名。语域把握：收信人为教授，语气应礼貌、尊敬；因属私人拜访，表达可适当自然，不必过于正式拘谨。内容要点：表达歉意并简要说明取消原因；主动提出改期会面，表达期待。【参考范文】Dear Professor Smith,I am writing to apologize for not being able to visit you as planned, since I have to cancel my travel plan for some reason. I am terribly sorry for any inconvenience this causes you and any changes that it necessitates in your current plans.I have been looking forward to seeing you since we made the appointment. Unexpectedly, I was asked to substitute for a classmate who suddenly fell ill to attend an important meeting.If it is possible, I would like to reschedule our appointment to a time convenient for you. Thank you for understanding in this matter.Looking forward to your reply.Sincerely yours,Li Ming【写作储备】道歉信常用表达开篇：说明写作目的I want to write you a letter to apologize.Please accept my sincere apology for…Please accept this letter as my formal apology for what happened on…中间段：说明理由 / 提出补救措施It was not my intention to cause any damage or inconvenience.I would try to offer an explanation for my behavior/what happened, although this is by no means an excuse.Would it be convenient for you if…?Would you prefer to…?结尾：再次表示歉意，请求原谅I sincerely thank you for hearing me out. Again, I am sorry for what happened.Again, I deeply apologize for the problems my actions caused, and I hope I can work to make it right.I am sorry to…, and hope that this has not caused you any great inconvenience.",
