          "stem": "将下列英文材料译成中文。",
          "body": "It is easy to underestimate English writer James Herriot. He had such a pleasant, readable style that one might think that anyone could imitate it. How many times have I heard people say, “I could write a book, I just haven’t the time” Easily said. Not so easily done. James Herriot, contrary to popular opinion did not find it easy in his early days of, as he put it, “having a go at the writing game”. While he obviously had an abundance of natural talent, the final polished work that he gave to the world was the result of years of practicing, re-writing and reading. Like the majority of authors, he had to suffer many disappointments and rejections along the way, but these made him all the more determined to succeed. Everything he achieved in life was earned the hard way and his success in the literary field was no exception.",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "【原文解析】一、文本来源与主旨节选自传记《真实的吉米·哈利：我父亲的回忆录》（1999）核心观点：破除“吉米·哈利文风易模仿”的误解，强调其成就源于长期磨砺语言特征：用词平实但多复合句，需注意逻辑衔接与中文意合表达二、翻译难点处理“having a go at the writing game”直译“尝试写作游戏”保留口语感，括号补充“正如他所说”明示引用属性自然语序调整将英语被动式\"it is easy to underestimate\"转化为中文主动表达“人们很容易低估”“the final polished work\"译为“精炼作品”，以四字结构浓缩“反复打磨”的隐含义文化适配“James Herriot\"统一译为读者熟悉的“吉米·哈利”（其作品《万物有灵且美》中文版用名）“rejections\"具体化为“退稿”，符合中文出版语境三、修辞对应策略谚语化处理：“Easily said. Not so easily done.” → “说起来容易。做起来可没那么容易。”递进强调：“all the more determined” → “更加下定决心”，通过“更加”强化对比首尾呼应：末句“也不例外”与开篇“很容易低估”形成逻辑闭环四、风格统一性全程使用“吉米·哈利”保持译名一致文学术语统一：“readable style”译“通俗易懂”，“natural talent”译“天赋异禀”保留原文谦抑语气，如“显然”“多少次的”等副词处理",
