          "stem": "将下列英文材料译成中文。",
          "body": "It’s almost impossible to go through life without experiencing some kind of failure. But, the wonderful thing about failure is that it’s entirely up to us to decide how to look at it.\nWe can choose to see failure as the end of the world.” Or, we can look at failure as the incredible learning experience that it often is. Every time we fail at something, we can choose to look for the lesson we’re meant to learn. These lessons are very important; they’re how we grow, and how we keep from making that same mistake again. Failures stop us only if we let them.\nFailure can also teach us things about ourselves that we would never have learned otherwise. For instance, failure can help you discover how strong a person you are. Failing at something can help you discover your truest friends, or help you find unexpected motivation to succeed.",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "【原文解析】一、总体分析文本来源：职场建议类网站MindTools文章《Overcoming Fear of Failure》中\"The Definition of Failure\"章节节选核心主题：探讨失败的积极意义，倡导以成长型思维面对挫折语言特点：生活化论述，多采用第二人称拉近读者距离存在\"end of the world\"等隐喻表达“incredible learning experience\"等抽象概念需要具体化转换二、重点词汇解析go through life → “人生历程”（动态过程表述）incredible learning experience → “宝贵的学习经历”（形容词具体化处理）keep from → “避免”（动词短语简洁化）unexpected motivation → “意想不到的动力”（保留原文意外性）三、句式结构分析“It’s entirely up to us…” 结构 → 转化为中文典型判断句\"完全取决于…”排比结构\"discover…/help you find…\" → 统一处理为\"发现…/找到…“保持节奏一致条件状语从句\"only if we let them” → 转换为\"只有…才…“强调句式四、翻译策略文化适应：将\"end of the world\"译为\"世界末日\"保留原文夸张修辞语序调整：英语复合句拆分为中文流水句，如原文最后长句分译为三个并列短句概念显化：“things about ourselves\"具体化为\"更了解自己”五、难点处理处理\"they’re how we grow\"时采用\"借此成长\"实现代词具体化“would never have learned otherwise\"通过\"不经历失败绝对不可能\"实现双重否定转换保持\"truest friends\"情感色彩译为\"最真的朋友\"而非字面\"最真实”",
