          "stem": "将下列英文材料译成中文。",
          "body": "With the smell of coffee and fresh bread floating in the air, stalls bursting with colorful vegetables and tempting cheeses, and the buzz of friendly chats, farmers’ markets are a feast for the senses. They also provide an opportunity to talk to the people responsible for growing or raising your food, support your local economy and pick up fresh seasonal produce — all at the same time. Farmers’ markets are usually weekly or monthly events, most often with outdoor stalls, which allow farmers or producers to sell their food directly to customers. The size or regularity of markets can vary from season to season, depending on the area’s agricultural calendar, and you’re likely to find different produce on sale at different times of the year. By cutting out the middlemen, the farmers secure more profit for their produce. Shoppers also benefit from seeing exactly where — and to who — their money is going.",
          "options": [],
          "answer": "空气中飘散着咖啡与新鲜面包的香气，摊位上堆满色彩缤纷的蔬菜与诱人奶酪，此起彼伏的友好交谈声萦绕耳畔——农夫市集堪称一场感官盛宴。这里不仅让您有机会与食物种植者面对面交流，还能助力本地经济发展，并采购到新鲜时令农产品，三者可同步实现。这类市集通常每周或每月举办，多以露天摊位形式呈现，使农户能直接向消费者销售产品。市场规模与举办频率会随季节变化，取决于当地农事周期，因此不同时节您可能发现各具特色的农产品。通过减少中间环节，农户能为产品争取更高利润。而消费者也能清晰感知自己的资金流向——确切知道惠及了哪些群体。",
